{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1198,"text":"I'm going to tell you the story of a song."},{"time":3864,"text":"I was in Madrid one night in 2002"},{"time":8282,"text":"with my teacher and friend Joaquín Sabina,"},{"time":10609,"text":"when he said he had something to give me."},{"time":13599,"text":"He said,"},{"time":14965,"text":"\"Jorge, I have some lines\nthat you need to put into a song."},{"time":18346,"text":"Take these down, take these down.\""},{"time":20029,"text":"I looked on the table but all I found\nwas a circular coaster,"},{"time":23057,"text":"on which I wrote the lines\nmy teacher dictated."},{"time":25433,"text":"They were four lines that went like this:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":27930,"text":"\"I am a Jewish Moor\nliving among Christians"},{"time":31291,"text":"I don't know who my God is,\nnor who my brothers are.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":36357,"text":"Those lines really made\nan impression on me."},{"time":39402,"text":"I said, \"What beautiful lyrics,\nJoaquín. Did you write them?\""},{"time":42410,"text":"He said no, they were by another composer\nnamed Chicho Sánchez Ferlosio,"},{"time":47912,"text":"who was less known than Joaquín,\nbut also a great poet."},{"time":51732,"text":"These lines came to me at a time"},{"time":53316,"text":"where I had been wanting\nto express something for a while,"},{"time":56146,"text":"but didn't quite know how."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57810,"text":"I was getting up to leave\nand go home to write,"},{"time":60720,"text":"when Joaquín stopped me\nand said, \"Hang on, hang on,\""},{"time":63234,"text":"and presented me with this challenge:"},{"time":65982,"text":"\"Write the stanzas for this song"},{"time":69001,"text":"in Décimas.\""},{"time":71086,"text":"Now, at this point in my life,"},{"time":73601,"text":"I still wasn't completely\nsure what Décimas were,"},{"time":77397,"text":"but I was too embarrassed\nto tell my teacher I didn't know."},{"time":81683,"text":"So I put on my best\n\"Yeah, I totally understand\" face,"},{"time":85392,"text":"and went home to look up\nwhat Décimas were."},{"time":88155,"text":"I learned that a Décima is a type of verse"},{"time":91659,"text":"that only exists in Spanish,"},{"time":93098,"text":"and that it has 10 lines."},{"time":94386,"text":"It's very, very complex --"},{"time":96411,"text":"perhaps the most complex style of stanza\nthat we have in Spanish."},{"time":99605,"text":"It also has a very concrete\ndate of origin,"},{"time":102088,"text":"which is very rare for a style of stanza."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104446,"text":"The Décima was invented in Spain in 1591,"},{"time":109693,"text":"by a guy named Vicente Espinel,\na musician and poet from Málaga."},{"time":115448,"text":"And listen to this coincidence:\nhe was the same guy"},{"time":118922,"text":"who added the sixth string"},{"time":120638,"text":"to what would later be called\nthe Spanish guitar."},{"time":122965,"text":"This string right here --"},{"time":124355,"text":"it's called the \"bordona.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":126604,"text":"From Spain, the Décima, with its 10 lines,"},{"time":130072,"text":"crosses over to America,\njust like the Spanish guitar,"},{"time":134903,"text":"but in contrast to the Décima,"},{"time":136457,"text":"the Spanish guitar continues to live today"},{"time":138930,"text":"on both sides of the Atlantic."},{"time":140643,"text":"But the Décima, in Spain, its birthplace,"},{"time":143759,"text":"disappeared; it died out."},{"time":146213,"text":"It died out about 200 years ago,"},{"time":148556,"text":"and yet in Latin America,\nfrom Mexico to Chile,"},{"time":153244,"text":"all our countries maintain\nsome form of the Décima"},{"time":157222,"text":"in our popular traditions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160331,"text":"In each place, they've given it\na different name,"},{"time":162669,"text":"and set it to different music."},{"time":164756,"text":"It has a lot of different names --\nmore than 20 in total on the continent."},{"time":169715,"text":"In Mexico, for example,\nit's called the \"Son Jarocho,\""},{"time":172833,"text":"\"Canto de mejorana\" in Panama;"},{"time":174662,"text":"\"Galerón\" in Venezuela;"},{"time":176240,"text":"\"Payada\" in Uruguay and Argentina;"},{"time":179297,"text":"\"Repentismo\" in Cuba."},{"time":180735,"text":"In Peru, they call it the Peruvian Décima,"},{"time":183041,"text":"because the Décima becomes\nso integrated into our traditions,"},{"time":186164,"text":"that if someone asks, people\nfrom each place are completely convinced"},{"time":189721,"text":"that the Décima was invented\nin their country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192500,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":193873,"text":"It's also got a really surprising feature,"},{"time":196048,"text":"which is that despite the fact\nthat it developed independently"},{"time":199341,"text":"in each of the different countries,"},{"time":201402,"text":"it maintains even today,\n400 years after its creation,"},{"time":205804,"text":"exactly the same rhyme,\nsyllable and line structure --"},{"time":212996,"text":"the same structure Vicente Espinel gave it\nduring the Spanish Baroque period."},{"time":216727,"text":"Here's the structure --"},{"time":217932,"text":"I'll give you the basic idea\nand then later you can look online"},{"time":220982,"text":"and learn more about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223126,"text":"The Décima is ten lines long;\neach line has eight syllables."},{"time":227961,"text":"The first line rhymes\nwith the fourth and the fifth;"},{"time":230460,"text":"the second line, with the third;"},{"time":232032,"text":"the sixth line,\nwith the seventh and the tenth;"},{"time":234863,"text":"and the eighth line rhymes with the ninth."},{"time":237321,"text":"It's a bit complicated, to be honest."},{"time":240132,"text":"And me -- imagine me,\ntrying to write in Décimas."},{"time":244207,"text":"But it's not as complicated as it seems."},{"time":247063,"text":"Plus, it's amazing that it's survived\nwith the same structure"},{"time":250248,"text":"for more than four centuries."},{"time":252860,"text":"It's not that complicated, because it has\nan impressive musicality to it,"},{"time":256356,"text":"a type of musicality"},{"time":258796,"text":"that's very hard to describe technically."},{"time":262096,"text":"I prefer that you listen to it."},{"time":263713,"text":"So I'm going to recite a Décima,"},{"time":267282,"text":"one of the Décimas\nthat I wrote for this song."},{"time":273120,"text":"I'm going to ask that you concentrate\njust on the musicality of the rhymes."},{"time":278112,"text":"For those of you with headphones on --"},{"time":280053,"text":"I see that some of you are listening\nto the translation --"},{"time":285692,"text":"please take them off for a minute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287781,"text":"(English) Take your headphones off,\nit you have them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291408,"text":"(English) Forget about the meaning\nof the words for a few seconds,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":297449,"text":"(English) and then you'll put them back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299444,"text":"(English) Forget about the structure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301274,"text":"(Spanish) Forget about the structure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303086,"text":"(English) And just ... it's all about\nthe choreography of sound of the Décima."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308352,"text":"(Spanish) A choreography of sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312752,"text":"(Sings in Spanish) \"There is not one death\nthat does not cause me pain,"},{"time":316188,"text":"there are no winners,"},{"time":317249,"text":"here’s nothing but suffering\nand another life blown away."},{"time":320191,"text":"War is a terrible school\nno matter what the disguise,"},{"time":323592,"text":"forgive me for not enlisting\nunder any flag,"},{"time":326514,"text":"any daydream is worth more\nthan a sad piece of cloth.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":334021,"text":"That's a Décima."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336151,"text":"(English) You can put\nyour headphones back on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338482,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":339584,"text":"(English) Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340761,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":345356,"text":"I also applaud Vicente Espinel,\nbecause here it is 426 years later,"},{"time":348679,"text":"and the Décima lives on everywhere"},{"time":350430,"text":"in its original state."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351652,"text":"I wrote three like that one;\nyou just heard the second."},{"time":354276,"text":"I wrote the first one having only\nrecently learned how,"},{"time":356974,"text":"and it has some errors in terms of meter,"},{"time":359103,"text":"so it's not presentable\nin its current state."},{"time":361292,"text":"But the one I sang was good, more or less."},{"time":363935,"text":"So: What was it about?"},{"time":367472,"text":"What was the meaning behind those lines?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":369714,"text":"I had just returned from doing\na concert in Israel,"},{"time":374173,"text":"and I was very emotional over a problem\nthat hits really close to home,"},{"time":377914,"text":"which is the Israeli-Palestinian conflict."},{"time":380005,"text":"I'll explain: my dad's family is Jewish,"},{"time":382152,"text":"and my mom's family\nare non-practicing Christians."},{"time":385049,"text":"I was raised in a home\nwhere the two traditions lived together"},{"time":389632,"text":"more or less in harmony."},{"time":392788,"text":"It wasn't unusual to see my Jewish grandpa\ndressed as Santa Claus, for example,"},{"time":396599,"text":"or to see my non-Jewish grandpa\nat the synagogue wearing his kippah,"},{"time":399861,"text":"at family celebrations, wearing the same\nexpression that I probably had"},{"time":403300,"text":"when Sabina told me --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":404687,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":405751,"text":"that he had some Décima lines for me."},{"time":410166,"text":"For someone raised\nin that kind of environment,"},{"time":413821,"text":"it's especially painful to see\nthe difficulty the opposing parties have"},{"time":419056,"text":"in putting themselves in the other\nside's shoes even for a moment."},{"time":422267,"text":"So that's what I wrote about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424403,"text":"I already had the lyrics,"},{"time":425677,"text":"I had the form -- the Décima --\nand the content."},{"time":429127,"text":"I needed to write the music."},{"time":432140,"text":"I'll give you some context."},{"time":433594,"text":"I had only recently moved from Uruguay,\nwhere I'm from, to Spain."},{"time":438293,"text":"And I was feeling very raw with nostalgia,"},{"time":441139,"text":"like many of you here,\nwho are away from home."},{"time":445090,"text":"And I wanted my song\nto be very, very Uruguayan,"},{"time":448564,"text":"the most Uruguayan type of song\nthere is -- the milonga."},{"time":452310,"text":"So now, I had been studying the Décima,\nand after finding out"},{"time":457823,"text":"that everyone tried to claim\nthe Décima as their own,"},{"time":460407,"text":"that it was invented in their country,"},{"time":462299,"text":"it made me wonder:"},{"time":463477,"text":"What does it mean when we say\nthe milonga is Uruguayan?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":466116,"text":"The milonga has a rhythmic pattern\nthat we musicians call 3-3-2."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472310,"text":"(Counts out the beats) One two three,\none two three, one two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479918,"text":"And it has a characteristic emphasis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482443,"text":"(Sings)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":490924,"text":"But this characteristic rhythm pattern"},{"time":493679,"text":"comes from Africa."},{"time":495580,"text":"In the ninth century you could find it\nin the brothels of Persia,"},{"time":498714,"text":"and in the thirteenth,"},{"time":501331,"text":"in Spain, from where,\nfive centuries later,"},{"time":504017,"text":"it would cross over to America\nwith the African slaves."},{"time":507877,"text":"Meanwhile, in the Balkans,\nit encounters the Roma scale --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":512278,"text":"(Sings)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":519569,"text":"which in part, gives birth\nto klezmer music,"},{"time":523082,"text":"which Ukrainian Jewish immigrants\nbring to Brooklyn, New York."},{"time":527848,"text":"They sing it in their banquet halls."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530711,"text":"(Sings \"Hava Nagila\")"}]},{"cues":[{"time":537485,"text":"And their neighbor,\nan Argentine kid of Italian origin"},{"time":540435,"text":"named Astor Piazzolla,"},{"time":542725,"text":"hears it,"},{"time":544767,"text":"assimilates it"},{"time":546318,"text":"and transforms the tango\nof the second half of the 20th century"},{"time":549343,"text":"with his ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550520,"text":"(Counts out the beats) One two three,\none two three, one two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554025,"text":"(Sings \"Adios Nonino\")"}]},{"cues":[{"time":562114,"text":"He also played it on his bandoneon,\na 19th-century German instrument"},{"time":566829,"text":"created for churches\nthat couldn't afford to buy organs,"},{"time":570980,"text":"and that ends up, incredibly,\nin Río de la Plata,"},{"time":573371,"text":"forming the very essence\nof the tango and the milonga,"},{"time":577482,"text":"in the very same way another instrument\njust as important as the bandoneon did:"},{"time":582525,"text":"the Spanish guitar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584100,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":596457,"text":"To which, by the way,\nVicente Espinel, in the 16th century,"},{"time":599305,"text":"added a sixth string."},{"time":600581,"text":"It's amazing how all these things\nare coming full circle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603475,"text":"What have I learned in these 15 years\nsince the song was born"},{"time":606379,"text":"from going all over the world\nwith four lines written on a coaster"},{"time":609739,"text":"from a bar in Madrid?"},{"time":612553,"text":"That Décimas,"},{"time":614691,"text":"the milonga,"},{"time":615955,"text":"songs, people --"},{"time":618461,"text":"the closer you get to them,"},{"time":620438,"text":"the more complex their identity becomes,"},{"time":623605,"text":"and the more nuances and details appear."},{"time":626818,"text":"I learned that identity\nis infinitely dense,"},{"time":629991,"text":"like an infinite series of real numbers,"},{"time":632567,"text":"and that even if you get very close"},{"time":634339,"text":"and zoom in,"},{"time":635521,"text":"it never ends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638467,"text":"Before I sing you a song and say goodbye,"},{"time":643064,"text":"allow me to tell you one last story."},{"time":645362,"text":"Not long ago, we were in Mexico\nafter a concert."},{"time":650902,"text":"And since the concert promoters know me,"},{"time":653187,"text":"they knew I was a Décima freak\nand that everywhere I go I ask about it,"},{"time":657135,"text":"insisting on hearing Décima artists."},{"time":658897,"text":"So they organized a son jarocho show\nfor me at their house."},{"time":664096,"text":"If you recall, the son jarocho\nis one of the styles of music"},{"time":668735,"text":"that uses Décimas in its verses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672552,"text":"When these amazing musicians\nfinished playing"},{"time":676388,"text":"what is for me, something amazing,\nwhich is the son jarocho,"},{"time":679290,"text":"they finished playing and were ..."},{"time":680979,"text":"I went up to greet them, really excited,"},{"time":683222,"text":"getting ready to thank them\nfor their gift of music,"},{"time":687490,"text":"and this young kid says to me --"},{"time":691443,"text":"and he says it with the best\nof intentions -- he says,"},{"time":694337,"text":"\"We're very proud, sir, to be keeping\nalive the purest origins"},{"time":701325,"text":"of our Mexican identity.\""},{"time":704418,"text":"And to tell you the truth,\nI didn't really know what to say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707358,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":708411,"text":"I stood there looking at him.\nI gave him a hug and left, but ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711600,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":712890,"text":"But he was right, too, though. Right?"},{"time":714899,"text":"In reality, the Décima is its origin,\nbut at the same time,"},{"time":717754,"text":"just like in the milonga\nand in the Décima,"},{"time":720148,"text":"are the roots of many more cultures\nfrom all over the place, like he said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726013,"text":"Later, when I got back to the hotel,\nI thought about it for a while."},{"time":729714,"text":"And I thought:"},{"time":730904,"text":"things only look pure"},{"time":735093,"text":"if you look at them from far away."},{"time":738041,"text":"It's very important\nto know about our roots,"},{"time":741410,"text":"to know where we come from,\nto understand our history."},{"time":745456,"text":"But at the same time, as important\nas knowing where we're from,"},{"time":748478,"text":"is understanding that deep down,"},{"time":752078,"text":"we're all from nowhere"},{"time":754062,"text":"and a little bit from everywhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":755711,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756960,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":766210,"text":"This is \"The milonga of the Jewish Moor.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":770178,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":782636,"text":"(Sings)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":784661,"text":"For every wall a lament\nin Jerusalem the golden"}]},{"cues":[{"time":792236,"text":"and 100 wasted lives\nfor every commandment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799536,"text":"I am dust in your wind\nand although I bleed through your wound,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":807047,"text":"and every beloved stone\nhas my deepest affection,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":813748,"text":"there is not a stone in the world\nworth more than a human life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822491,"text":"I am a Jewish Moor\nwho lives among Christians"}]},{"cues":[{"time":829834,"text":"I don't know who my God is,\nnor who my brothers are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":838211,"text":"I don't know who my God is,\nnor who my brothers are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847659,"text":"There is not one death that does not\ncause me pain, there are no winners"}]},{"cues":[{"time":855020,"text":"there's nothing but suffering\nand another life blown away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":862496,"text":"War is a terrible school\nno matter what the disguise,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":869862,"text":"forgive me for not enlisting\nunder any flag,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":876531,"text":"any daydream is worth more\nthan a sad piece of cloth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":885126,"text":"I am a Jewish Moor\nwho lives among Christians"}]},{"cues":[{"time":892342,"text":"I don't know who my God is,\nnor who my brothers are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":900511,"text":"I don't know who my God is,\nnor who my brothers are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":913858,"text":"And nobody has my permission\nfor killing in my name,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":921143,"text":"a man is but a man\nand if there is a God, this was his wish,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":928540,"text":"the very ground I tread\nwill live on, once I am gone"}]},{"cues":[{"time":935912,"text":"on my way to oblivion, and all doctrines\nwill suffer the same fate,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":942126,"text":"and there is not one nation\nthat has not proclaimed itself"}]},{"cues":[{"time":947147,"text":"the chosen people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951807,"text":"I am a Jewish Moor\nwho lives among Christians"}]},{"cues":[{"time":958806,"text":"I don't know who my God is,\nnor who my brothers are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":967052,"text":"I don't know who my God is,\nnor who my brothers are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972903,"text":"I am a Jewish Moor\nwho lives among Christians"}]},{"cues":[{"time":980084,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":981508,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":982698,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}